{
  "texts": [
    "For non-abelian N we may always view G/K as a totally geodesic submanifold of det -1 (±1)/O(n).In our second main result, we apply Theorem A to produce large families of Ricci solitons by solving the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (4).",
    "It turns out that all expanding solitons corresponding to solutions with dim B ≤ 1 are locally homogeneous (see Section 3.3), so the first interesting case for us is when B is a closed surface.",
    "In this case, a result of Labourie [Lab08] allows us to solve the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations for a certain class of representations.Theorem B.",
    "Let B 2 be a closed surface, and suppose that ρ ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), SL n (R)) lies in a Hitchin component.",
    "Then, on the ρ-twisted principal bundle M = B × ρ R n there exists an affine expanding Ricci soliton metric.The Hitchin components, discovered in [Hit92], are certain distinguished connected components of the space of representations Hom(π 1 (B), G)/G for an adjoint split semisimple Lie group G, which in some sense generalise the Teichmüller space component in the case G = PGL 2 (R)."
  ]
}